TopicTitle: Sometimes game fails to load (hangs on loading Ion Engine part)

Articles.Content:
Hi!

KSP sometimes fail to start properly. It always stops at loading the Ion Engine part definition.

But what is most strage is that the KSP loading process just stops but the KSP aplication itself doesn't hang. The goffy text on loading screen is still switching between different statements.

KSP is compleetly unmoded and the problem isn't presistant.

I'm launcing 32 bit version of KSP on Windows 7 64 bit.

Sometimes KSP fails to load properly and sometimes it loads just fine.

Now based on KSP.log the part fails to load becouse "The requested value 'Engine' was not found."

Here is part of KSP.log regarding of loading parts definitions.

If the problem is inconsistent, it's likely the origin of the problem is not KSP itself... It may depend where you've installed KSP (if you have the non-Steam version), which antivirus you have running, and possibly also on your operating system and installed drivers. Needless to say, ensure everything is thoroughly up to date.

Considering it's having trouble loading up some of its .cfg files, I would suspect an issue with KSP being installed to a location where Windows applies restrictive permissions, or possibly an antivirus examining KSP as it runs.

KSP is installed in a folder witn full acces so no read/write limitations. Yes this is a non-steam version of KSP).

I'm sure that my antivirus software (ESET Smart Security 5) isn't causing any problems or else I would see this in my AV software logs.

Anywhay after quick searching of KSP forums I saw athleast one person mentioning similar problem but it was in the context of another thread regarding the KSP update. But I couldn't find any standalone thread about this ise nor any further infromation therefore I have created this thread.

Now it is posible that unintsaling and reinstaling the KSP might solve this problem (I have updated it from previous version) but I decided not to try this just yet becouse now I'm still in positio to offer you guys with some more information about this.

If needed I can make a Memory Dump of the KSP application once it get stuck at this bug. I can also save short stack history for each of the KSP threads.

There are actually read/write limitations on a lot of folders in Windows, despite it claiming there are in fact none. DEP appears to be the root of the cause there, and it's been a problem for a while. Just to be sure, if KSP is on the Desktop, or in any of your user folders (Documents, Downloads, Pictures, etc.) or anywhere in Program Files, it's a good idea to make a copy in a new location for testing purposes. Those locations have been known to cause issues, regardless of how their normal permissions are set. DEP is a pain in the neck, believe me.

Anyhow, for testing purposes it might also be worth simply disconnecting from the Internet briefly and disabling your AV to run KSP. Usually you should see it in the logs, aye, but we're just being thorough, No sense overlooking something simple and going on a wild goose chase.

Most of us tend not to be experienced enough to find the memory dumps useful, in truth. I'm not sure if Squad's support staff (that's not us; Squad's support staff monitor the email address [email protected]) could use it, but in any case we can always have a look. Perhaps we'll be able to see something of use.

Confirmed, same issue for me. TLDR: Patching not successful. Reinstall fixes issue. Below is full account, maybe most of it known issues.

In my case, I updated/patched Win x64 0.23 to 0.90 using Launcher, noticed Rsync error in the patch report but didn't otherwise see errors and didn't save what I saw. Update button in Launcher was disabled after this patching, so I assumed it was ok.

After updating, game would not load past ionEngine when starting via Launcher, same result when starting using KSP_64.exe. Game did successfully start when running KSP.exe, but weird stuff in game like duplicates (x2) in the parts list in the hangar. Obviously things were messed up.

Downloaded the 0.90 Win x64 zip file. Uncompressed and ran Launcher. Update button was active so I clicked it. Patching completed with one error, some files/attrs were not transferred, rename output_log.txt: device or resource busy. Started game with Launcher, game loaded successfully. Started Career Mode, all buildings came in fully upgraded. Everything else looks right at a glance (no more duplicate parts). Adjusting volume settings also reduced window resolution.

Downloaded the 0.90 Win x32 zip file. Uncompressed and ran launcher. Update button disabled so launched game. Started career mode, buildings are not upgraded, everything else looks right at a glance. Again, adjusting volume also reduced window resolution.

Yeah, most of those are known issues with the x64 version and/or not fully deleting previous versions of KSP (the duplicate parts come from multiple entries in the Gamedata folder when the parts got shuffled around). But it's interesting that the launcher sometimes doesn't like the ion engine - why that part in particular? Why does the Launcher not like it, but the .exe work fine? We may never know..
